gland by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Lovestick was born in 1300, in Hallon, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Stephen Lovestick, was 30 and his mother, Mrs. Stephen Lovestick, was 26. He married Mrs. William Lovestick in 1337, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1369, in his hometown, at the age of 69."},"et":{"1300–1369":"1300–1369","1305–1338":"1305–1338","1338–1386":"1338–1386","1270–1345":"1270–1345","1275–1300":"1275–1300","1338":"1338","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1369":"1369","1345":"1345","1300":"1300","Aft 1300":"pärast 1300","1386":"1386","1275":"1275","Aft 1338":"pärast 1338","1270":"1270","after 1300":"pärast 1300","Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Hallon, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hallon, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1300–1369":"1300–1369","1305–1338":"1305–1338","1338–1386":"1338–1386","1270–1345":"1270–1345","1275–1300":"1275–1300","1338":"1338","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1369":"1369","1345":"1345","1300":"1300","Aft 1300":"1300 jälkeen","1386":"1386","1275":"1275","Aft 1338":"1338 jälkeen","1270":"1270","after 1300":"1300 jälkeen","Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Hallon, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hallon, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuninga